monia under both classic and phosphate-coupled conditions, (iv) environmental microcompartmentalization (wet-dry cycling, pH gradients, mineral-organic adsorption) that enable concentration and selectivity, (v) additional imidazole-production routes (Or\u00f3 et al., Ritson & Sutherland) and spark-driven settings as feedstock reservoirs, (vi) stabilization and protection by mineral surfaces (montmorillonite, pyrite), and (vii) biochemical assembly including peptide formation. Hub molecules are imidazole-4-acetaldehyde, erythrose, HCN, and imidazole-4-glycol. Ten pathways are designed with multiple environmental modes and convergence points as required by the literature.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "C4H8O4", "iupac_name": "2,3,4-trihydroxybutanal", "common_name": "Erythrose", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C4H8O4/c5-1-2-3(6)4(7)8/h1-4,6-8H,2H2", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "CH5N3", "iupac_name": "Formamidine", "common_name": "Formamidine", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH5N3/c2-1-3-4/h2H,1H2,(H2,3,4)", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_003", "formula": "CH2O", "iupac_name": "Methanal", "common_name": "Formaldehyde", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2O/c1-2/h1H2", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_004", "formula": "NH3", "iupac_name": "Azane", "common_name": "Ammonia", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H3N/h1H3", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Hydrothermal"}, {"id": "mol_005", "formula": "HCN", "iupac_name": "Hydrogen cyanide", "common_name": "Hydrogen cyanide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CN/c1-2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_006", "formula": "C4H8N2O2", "iupac_name": "imidazole-4-glycol", "common_name": "Imidazole-4-glycol", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C4H8N2O2/c7-2-1-6-3-5-4(8)7/h1-3,7-8H,2H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_007", "formula": "C4H8N2O", "iupac_name": "imidazole-4-ethanol", "c